ef%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-what-to-do-hr-exec-apply-job-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformance%20improvement%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20different%20perspectives%3A%20I've%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpip-start-looking-job-good-bad-managers-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eput%20people%20on%20PIPs%3C%2Fa%3E%20myself%2C%20coached%20people%20through%20them%2C%20and%20had%20direct%20reports%20put%20their%20direct%20reports%20on%20PIPs%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20on%20a%20PIP%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20feel%20unempowered%20because%20they're%20scary%20and%20uncomfortable.%20People%20make%20mistakes%20when%20on%20PIPS%20that%20can%20ultimately%20cost%20them%20their%20jobs.%20Here%20are%20four%20of%20them%20to%20be%20aware%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bec60ffb-1b44-4b68-9168-7f41f087a596%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Don't%20get%20defensive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20mistake%20people%20make%20when%20they%20get%20put%20on%20a%20PIP%20is%20they%20get%20defensive.%20They%20don't%20realize%20that%20you%20can't%20argue%20your%20way%20out%20of%20a%20PIP%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can't%20undo%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPIPs%20are%20premeditated%20and%20aren't%20just%20done%20on%20a%20whim.%20If%20a%20manager%20is%20trying%20to%20indicate%20that%20you%20have%20a%20performance%20challenge%2C%20getting%20defensive%20is%20the%20worst%20thing%20you%20can%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20say%20you're%20an%20engineer%20and%20not%20hitting%20your%20deadlines.%20You%20don't%20want%20to%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20because%20the%20product%20team%20didn't%20give%20me%20a%20clear%20spec%2C%26quot%3B%20or%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20because%20we%20cut%20the%20budgets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20you%20think%20your%20manager%20is%20wrong%2C%20their%20feedback%20is%20false%2C%20or%20you%20disagree%20entirely%2C%20you%20must%20try%20to%20understand%20their%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20that%20you'll%20never%20get%20a%20chance%20to%20share%20your%20side%3B%20you%20usually%20have%20months%20to%20do%20that%20with%20whoever%20put%20you%20on%20the%20PIP%2C%20as%20they%20are%20the%20person%20who%20you%20ultimately%20should%20try%20to%20convince%20why%20you%20shouldn't%20be%20on%20one.%20Still%2C%20you%20have%20to%20listen%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGet%20curious%20and%20seek%20feedback.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20come%20out%20on%20the%20other%20side%2C%20you%20must%20listen%20and%20approach%20it%20with%20an%20open%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2271c43e1f-de4c-4e0f-8078-4d80b8ccd5d8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Don't%20tarnish%20your%20reputation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20mistake%20you%20shouldn't%20make%20is%20tarnishing%20your%20reputation.%20Your%20reputation%20belongs%20to%20you%2C%20and%20it%20transcends%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20way%20people%20hurt%20their%20reputation%20is%20by%20thinking%3A%20%3Cem%3EYou%20know%20what%3F%20I'll%20get%20fired%20in%20three%20months%20anyway%2C%20so%20I'm%20just%20going%20to%20quit.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20manager%20might%20just%20think%20the%20dynamics%20are%20wrong%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20might%20still%20think%20you're%20great.%20Or%2C%20maybe%20your%20company%20realizes%20you're%20just%20in%20the%20wrong%20department.%20If%20you%20work%20at%20a%20big%20enough%20organization%2C%20there%20may%20be%20other%20open%20roles%20that%20you're%20a%20better%20fit%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eee808cb-6cbb-4536-8f58-d1057acb4942%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Don't%20forget%20to%20learn%20from%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20sit%20on%20a%20PIP%2C%20you%20may%20think%20that%20you%20can't%20fix%20it%20or%20that%20it's%20irreparable.%20Even%20if%20you%20feel%20that%20to%20be%20true%2C%20don't%20miss%20the%20opportunity%20to%20improve%20and%20learn%20from%20the%20feedback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPIPs%20usually%20come%20with%20a%20timeline%20and%20are%20very%20structured.%20Essentially%2C%20they're%20building%20a%20paper%20trail%20for%20why%20they're%20eliminating%20your%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they're%20giving%20you%20feedback%2C%20use%20it%20as%20a%20learning%20opportunity.%20Take%20that%20time%20to%20build%20those%20muscles%20because%20even%20if%20learning%20doesn't%20save%20you%20in%20your%20current%20job%2C%20it%20will%20help%20you%20in%20your%20next%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnderstand%20that%20getting%20feedback%20is%20a%20chance%20to%20grow%20and%20recognize%20when%20you%20can%20improve.%20Although%20all%20feedback%20is%20important%2C%20PIP%20feedback%20will%20cost%20you%20a%20job%20if%20you%20don't%20address%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225182a05c-e636-460a-9c13-e95b2deb98a1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Don't%20forget%20to%20self-promote%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20work%2C%20sometimes%20people%20assume%20that%20if%20they%20come%20in%20and%20do%20hard%20work%2C%20everyone%20will%20notice.%20That's%20just%20not%20true.%20Usually%2C%20those%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fan-introverts-guide-to-self-promotion-at-work-5-tips-that-wont-make-you-wince-2014-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etactically%20self-promote%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20make%20sure%20those%20who%20placed%20them%20on%20the%20PIP%20are%20aware%20of%20their%20wins%20and%20contributions%20tend%20to%20move%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20put%20on%20a%20PIP%20and%20feel%20you're%20doing%20incredible%20things%2C%20you%20might%20think%2C%20%3Cem%3EHow%20do%20they%20not%20know%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%20Maybe%20the%20mistake%20is%20that%20you're%20too%20humble%20and%20letting%20your%20team%20have%20all%20the%20credit%2C%20so%20they%20think%20you're%20not%20doing%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20on%20a%20PIP%2C%20ask%20yourself%3A%20%3Cem%3EWhat%20are%20you%20doing%20weekly%20to%20ensure%20they%20don't%20forget%20you%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%20Then%2C%20remind%20them%20regularly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDocument%20everything%20you're%20doing.%20Send%20a%20weekly%20update%20via%20email%20or%20Slack%20if%20that%20works%20better%20for%20your%20team%2C%20and%20also%20set%20up%20regular%20check-ins%20with%20your%20manager.%20You%20want%20continual%20feedback.%20Remember%2C%20they're%20not%20waiting%20until%20the%20end%20of%20the%20PIP%20to%20form%20their%20opinion%20on%20your%20performance%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20forming%20it%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a290d7e5-ca23-47ae-a136-849ca3b2dd9c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20you're%20fired%2C%20go%20gracefully%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20let%20go%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20PIP%2C%20you%20have%20to%20accept%20it.%20Relationships%20go%20with%20you%2C%20so%20try%20to%20build%20as%20many%20as%20you%20can%2C%20maintain%20your%20identity%2C%20learn%20what%20you%20can%20from%20the%20experience%2C%20leave%20gracefully%2C%20adjust%2C%20and%20start%20looking%20for%20something%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20stay%2C%20understand%20that%20it's%20not%20likely%20you%20got%20off%20the%20PIP%20and%20are%20automatically%20good%20to%20go.%20You%20received%20feedback%20about%20things%20they%20were%20worried%20about%2C%20so%20continue%20to%20build%20their%20confidence%20in%20you%20and%20make%20them%20feel%20good%20about%20why%20you're%20there.%20Reiterate%20why%20it%20was%20the%20right%20decision%20to%20keep%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-never-make-on-pip-from-teal-ceo-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741169102000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c721c9b1834fe31166165b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-never-make-on-pip-from-teal-ceo-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20CEO%20of%20Teal%20and%20former%20WeWork%20exec%20David%20Fano%20says%20if%20you're%20put%20on%20a%20PIP%