5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBaby%20boomers%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20simultaneously%20be%20aging%20out%20of%20the%20market%20(economist-speak%20for%20dying)%2C%20freeing%20up%20millions%20of%20homes%20nationwide.%20Unless%20immigration%20picks%20up%20dramatically%20to%20compensate%2C%20the%20combination%20of%20more%20supply%20and%20less%20demand%20could%20cause%20home%20prices%20to%20flatline%20or%20even%20drop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20get%20me%20wrong%3A%20Cheaper%20housing%20is%20a%20good%20thing.%20But%20while%20a%20dip%20in%20home%20prices%20probably%20sounds%20like%20a%20godsend%20to%20the%20millions%20of%20renters%20hoping%20to%20become%20owners%2C%20it%20could%20be%20devastating%20for%20those%20who%20bought%20a%20place%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20These%20homeowners%2C%20mostly%20millennials%2C%20are%20counting%20on%20their%20properties%20to%20grow%20in%20value%20and%20deliver%20a%20hefty%20financial%20return%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-investment-market-mortgage-rates-baby-boomers-down-payment-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egilded%20path%20enjoyed%20by%20baby%20boomers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Like%20generations%20before%20them%2C%20millennials%20have%20tied%20up%20most%20of%20their%20wealth%20in%20their%20homes%2C%20which%20they'll%20rely%20upon%20to%20fuel%20their%20retirements%20or%20fund%20the%20purchases%20of%20bigger%20places%20down%20the%20line.%20Instead%2C%20when%20it%20finally%20comes%20time%20for%20them%20to%20sell%2C%20they%20may%20find%20that%20their%20nest%20eggs%20have%20turned%20out%20a%20lot%20smaller%20than%20they'd%20hoped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPopulation%20trends%2C%20unlike%20the%20constant%20ups%20and%20downs%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20follow%20a%20steady%20drumbeat%3A%20People%20grow%20up%2C%20settle%20down%2C%20and%20eventually%20die.%20Demographics%20can't%20tell%20us%20exactly%20how%20many%20homes%20we'll%20need%20in%20a%20decade%20or%20two%2C%20but%20they%20can%20offer%20a%20pretty%20good%20idea.%20Builders%20and%20policymakers%2C%20however%2C%20haven't%20been%20great%20at%20reading%20the%20tea%20leaves.%20A%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rsfjournal.org%2Fcontent%2F11%2F1%2F86.full%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20a%20team%20of%20researchers%20led%20by%20Dowell%20Myers%2C%20a%20demographer%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%2C%20argues%20that%20the%20lever%20pullers%20who%20control%20the%20housing%20supply%20have%20been%20out%20of%20touch%20for%20decades%2C%20relying%20on%20old%20data%20or%20focusing%20too%20much%20on%20the%20short%20term%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20more%20distant%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20the%20current%20housing%20crunch.%20For%20years%2C%20demographic%20forecasts%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20a%20huge%20chunk%20of%20millennials%20would%20be%20looking%20to%20settle%20down%20in%20the%20late%202010s%2C%20signaling%20a%20need%20for%20a%20lot%20more%20houses.%20But%20homebuilding%20activity%20in%202011%20dropped%20to%20its%20lowest%20level%20in%2060%20years%2C%20and%20credit%20availability%20tightened%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20to%20get%20a%20mortgage%20and%20creating%20more%20pent-up%20homebuying%20demand.%20Cue%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-house-home-real-estate-mortgage-rates-rent-debt-boomers-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etough%20times%20for%20millennials%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20real%20estate%20experts%20are%20starting%20to%20pay%20more%20attention%20to%20the%20underlying%20realities.%20I%20recently%20had%20lunch%20with%20Nik%20Shah%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Home.LLC%2C%20a%20housing%20analytics%2C%20consulting%2C%20and%20AI%20conglomerate.%20Shah%20and%20his%20team%20have%20gained%20prominence%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%20for%20accurately%20predicting%20changes%20in%20home%20prices%20despite%20a%20tumultuous%20market.%20I%20was%20surprised%2C%20then%2C%20when%20instead%20of%20talking%20about%20the%20coming%20months%2C%20he%20mostly%20wanted%20to%20discuss%20the%20long%20term.%20Shah%20told%20me%20he's%20bullish%20on%20home%20prices%20for%20the%20next%20handful%20of%20years%2C%20forecasting%20mild%20year-over-year%20increases.%20But%20based%20on%20the%20demographic%20data%2C%20Shah%20expects%20home%20prices%20to%20stall%20out%20in%20the%202030s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDemographics%20play%20a%20critical%20role%20in%20home%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20Shah%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20right%20now%2C%20the%20future%20projections%20on%20demographics%20are%20not%20rosy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20factor%20is%20deaths.%20In%20the%20coming%20decade%2C%20baby%20boomers%20will%20begin%20%26quot%3Baging%20out%20of%20the%20market%26quot%3B%20in%20droves.%20The%20size%20of%20the%20generation's%20adult%20population%20is%20second%20only%20to%20millennials%2C%20with%20roughly%2066%20million%20members%20who%20range%20in%20age%20from%2061%20to%2079.%20But%20their%20numbers%20are%20projected%20to%20shrink%20by%20about%2023%25%2C%20or%2015.6%20million%20people%2C%20in%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20and%20by%20another%2023.4%20million%20people%20from%202035%20to%202045.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-markets-benefit-boomer-wealth-transfer-rust-belt-young-homebuyer-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoomers%20own%20about%2041%25%20of%20real%20estate%3C%2Fa%3E%20nationwide%2C%20worth%20roughly%20%2420%20trillion%2C%20per%20the%20Federal%20Reserve.%20Their%20exodus%20will%20represent%20a%20sea%20change%20in%20the%20housing%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20those%20boomer%20deaths%2C%20combined%20with%20a%20slight%20decline%20in%20birth%20rates%20over%20the%20next%20two%20decades%2C%20will%20work%20out%20to%20slower%20population%20growth.%20The%20result%20will%20be%20a%20lot%20less%20demand%20for%20homes.%20Data%20from%20the%20Harvard%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies%20indicates%20that%20the%20total%20number%20of%20households%20in%20the%20US%20is%20expected%20to%20increase%20by%208.6%20million%20over%20the%20next%2010%20years.%20In%20the%20past%20three%20decades%2C%20that%20figure%20ranged%20from%2010.1%20million%20households%2C%20in%20the%202010s%2C%20to%2013.5%20million%2C%20in%20the%201990s.%20From%202035%20to%202045%2C%20household%20growth%20is%20expected%20to%20retreat%20even%20more%2C%20to%20a%20net%20increase%20of%20just%205.1%20million%2C%20which%20would%20be%20the%20lowest%20growth%20rate%20in%20a%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20more%20deaths%20and%20fewer%20births%2C%20the%20total%20number%20of%20US-born%20people%20in%20the%20country%20will%20shrink.%20The%20trajectory%20of%20the%20country's%20population%2C%20Daniel%20McCue%2C%20a%20senior%20research%20associate%20at%20the%20center%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20report%2C%20will%20therefore%20be%20%26quot%3Bentirely%20dependent%20on%20future%20immigration.%26quot%3B%20Those%20household-growth%20projections%20from%20the%20Census%20Bureau%20assume%20that%20net%20immigration%20holds%20steady%20at%20873%2C000%20people%20a%20year%20for%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20roughly%20in%20line%20with%20the%20past%2030%20years.%20But%20even%20if%20you%20assume%20significantly%20higher%20immigration%2C%20McCue%20tells%20me%2C%20household%20growth%20is%20expected%20to%20decline%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20generation%20of%20new%20homeowners%20won't%20represent%20a%20steep%20dropoff%20in%20demand.%20Harvard%20JCHS%20estimates%20there%20are%20now%20roughly%2068%20million%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20aged%2016%20to%2030%2C%20compared%20to%2068.8%20million%20millennials.%20McCue%20says%20the%20real%20problem%20comes%20from%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20population%20equation%2C%20since%20a%20steady%20handoff%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-real-estate-investing-mistakes-buying-homes-early-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%20homebuyers%3C%2Fa%3E%20won't%20offset%20the%20wave%20of%20boomers%20exiting%20the%20housing%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20enough%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20pickup%20in%20losses%2C%20because%20the%20baby%20boomer%20generation%20is%20just%20so%20much%20bigger%20than%20previous%20generations%2C%26quot%3B%20McCue%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThe%20pickup%20in%20mortality%20is%20going%20to%20outpace%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20shifting%20demographics%2C%20the%20center%20says%20America%20probably%20needs%20to%20build%20about%2011.3%20million%20homes%20over%20the%20next%20decade%20and%20just%208%20million%20new%20units%20between%202035%20and%202045%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20demand%20from%20new%20households%20(not%20factoring%20in%20the%20current%20shortage).%20These%20are%20fairly%20modest%20goals%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%202010s%2C%20which%20included%20the%20weakest%20years%20for%20new%20construction%20in%20more%20than%20half%20a%20century%2C%20builders%20still%20finished%20almost%2010%20million%20units.%20In%20the%202000s%2C%20they%20built%2017%20million.%20As%20demand%20for%20homes%20slows%20down%2C%20McCue%20says%2C%20construction%20should%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20catch%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20possibility%20should%20sound%20tantalizing%20to%20anyone%20hoping%20for%20an%20end%20to%20our%20housing%20shortage.%20But%20the%20imbalance%20between%20supply%20and%20demand%20has%20fueled%20an%20extraordinary%20run-up%20in%20home%20values%20%E2%80%94%20if%20that%20lopsidedness%20goes%20away%2C%20millennial%20homeowners%20may%20not%20see%20the%20same%20financial%20windfalls%20as%20their%20predecessors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-adults-work-parents-bosses-children-homeownership-responsibility-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMillennials%20aren't%20young%20upstarts%3C%2Fa%3E%20anymore.%20In%202030%2C%20they'll%20range%20in%20age%20from%2034%20to%2049%2C%20according%20to%20Pew%20Research's%20cutoffs%2C%20which%20means%20many%20will%20be%20looking%20to%20move%20up%20the%20rungs%20of%20the%20housing%20ladder%20as%20they%20buy%20their%20first%20places%20or%20upgrade%20to%20bigger%20homes.%20They've%20already%20made%20up%20considerable%20ground%20in%20this%20department%2C%20with%20more%20than%20half%20the%20generation%20now%20owning%20their%20homes.%20For%20these%20fortunate%20millennials%2C%20the%20past%20few%20years%20of%20home-price%20gains%20have%20padded%20their%20net%20worths%20and%20contributed%20to%20a%20sunnier%20financial%20outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20things%20are%20looking%20up%2C%20that%20may%20not%20last.%20A%20slowdown%20in%20home-price%20growth%2C%20or%20even%20outright%20declines%2C%20could%20leave%20a%20large%20chunk%20of%20millennials%20in%20a%20weird%20spot.%20Sure%2C%20for%20those%20who%20don't%20yet%20own%20a%20home%2C%20a%20breather%20in%20home-price%20appreciation%20could%20offer%20a%20chance%20to%20play%20catch-up.%20But%20among%20the%20millennials%20who%20are%20actually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-saw-wealth-grow-double-during-pandemic-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoing%20pretty%20well%20financially%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20most%20wealth%20is%20tied%20up%20in%20real%20estate%20and%20retirement%20accounts.%20An%20analysis%20by%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20St.%20Louis%20suggests%20that%20from%202019%20to%202022%2C%20the%20typical%20person%20born%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20otherwise%20known%20as%20an%20elder%20millennial%2C%20saw%20the%20value%20of%20their%20assets%20balloon%20by%20a%20whopping%2057.3%25%2C%20even%20after%20adjusting%20for%20inflation.%20Most%20of%20that%20increase%20%E2%80%94%2041%20percentage%20points%20%E2%80%94%20came%20from%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20let's%20say%20household%20formation%20slows%20down%20as%20expected%2C%20relieving%20some%20of%20the%20pressure%20on%20home%20prices%20to%20keep%20going%20up%2C%20up%2C%20up.%20The%20team%20at%20Home.LLC%20projects%20that%20in%20this%20scenario%2C%20even%20if%20immigration%20holds%20steady%2C%20home%20prices%20will%20stay%20flat%2C%20maybe%20increasing%20by%20about%201%25%20in%20some%20years%20and%20dipping%20slightly%20in%20others.%20That's%20a%20long%20way%20from%20the%20kind%20of%20market%20crash%20we%20saw%20in%202008%2C%20but%20it%20would%20mean%20far%20less%20wealth%20gains%20for%20today's%20millennial%20homeowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20illustrate%20this%20tension%2C%20compare%20a%20hypothetical%20baby%20boomer%20with%20a%20hypothetical%20millennial.%20Each%20buys%20a%20%24300%2C000%20home%20during%20their%20heyday.%20The%20boomer%20bought%20the%20house%20in%201994.%20Thirty%20years%20later%2C%20it's%20fully%20paid%20off%20and%20sells%20for%20about%20%241.21%20million%20%E2%80%94%20a%20stunning%20gain%20of%20305%25%2C%20based%20on%20the%20typical%20home-price%20appreciation%20in%20the%20US%20over%20those%20decades.%20The%20millennial%20buys%20the%20house%20in%202010%20and%20also%20holds%20on%20to%20it%20for%2030%20years.%20Its%20value%20grows%20by%202.5%25%20each%20year%20from%202025%20to%202030%20and%20by%20just%200.5%25%20a%20year%20from%202031%20to%202040.%20The%20home%20ends%20up%20being%20worth%20about%20%24813%2C000%2C%20a%20171%25%20increase.%20That's%20nothing%20to%20sneeze%20at%2C%20but%20you'd%20take%20the%20boomer's%20gains%20any%20day%20of%20the%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BObviously%2C%20the%20difference%20is%20pretty%20huge%2C%26quot%3B%20Sid%20Samant%2C%20Home.LLC's%20lead%20economist%2C%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20the%20elder%20millennial%20in%20this%20example%20is%20lucky%2C%20because%20they%20got%20to%20ride%20out%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fhousing-market-home-prices-inventory-pandemic-mortgage-rates-fed-property-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehistoric%20home-value%20increases%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20the%20pandemic.%20In%20Home.LLC's%20model%2C%20someone%20who%20bought%20a%20house%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20say%2C%20a%20millennial%20who%20finally%20found%20their%20foothold%20in%20the%20housing%20market%20%E2%80%94%20would%20see%20their%20home's%20value%20increase%20by%20just%2031%25%20through%202040.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForecasting%20home%20prices%20a%20decade%20from%20now%20is%20a%20fraught%20endeavor.%20Nobody%20expected%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-millennials-housing-market-home-prices-mortgage-rates-inventory-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebaby%20boomers%20to%20stay%20in%20their%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20long%20as%20they%20have%2C%20throwing%20the%20housing%20market%20out%20of%20whack%20for%20everyone%20else.%20For%20policymakers%2C%20immigration%20is%20the%20easiest%20lever%20to%20pull%20in%20counteracting%20demographic%20realities%2C%20which%20also%20makes%20it%20the%20biggest%20question%20mark.%20And%20there's%20no%20way%20of%20knowing%20how%20future%20changes%20in%20the%20economy%20will%20alter%20construction%20activity%20or%20the%20homebuying%20calculus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20demographic%20change%20is%20inevitable.%20And%20even%20McCue%2C%20the%20Harvard%20researcher%20who%20lives%20and%20breathes%20this%20stuff%2C%20is%20still%20wrestling%20with%20the%20downstream%20effects%20of%20our%20aging%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20extent%20to%20which%20we're%20going%20to%20start%20losing%20households%20was%20very%20eye-opening%2C%26quot%3B%20McCue%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20still%20need%20to%20get%20our%20heads%20around%20the%20implications%20of%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20housing%20shortage%20does%20indeed%20go%20away%2C%20it%20will%20hardly%20be%20mourned.%20But%20any%20big%20shift%20usually%20comes%20with%20some%20collateral%20damage.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20it%20could%20be%20homeowning%20millennials%20who%20get%20burned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch