.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-trump-tariffs-trade-war-bond-market-yields-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etariffs%20could%20be%20long-lasting%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20US%20economy%20is%20in%20for%20%26quot%3Bshort-term%20pain%26quot%3B%20as%20tariffs%20fundamentally%20change%20the%20structure%20of%20the%20US%20economy%20by%20growing%20the%20domestic%20manufacturing%20industry%2C%20Apollo's%20Chief%20Economist%20Torsten%20Sl%C3%B8k%20said%20on%20a%20conference%20call%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20the%20areas%20of%20the%20market%20that'll%20see%20the%20biggest%20impacts%20if%20Trump%20continues%20to%20double%20down%20on%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ea704207-2632-4430-9128-e4150fae42fa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETariff%20winners%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETariffs%20aren't%20all%20doom%20and%20gloom.%20After%20all%2C%20they're%20meant%20to%20be%20protectionist%20policies%20that%20boost%20domestic%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20US%20equities%2C%20that%20means%20services%20are%20positioned%20to%20outperform%20consumer%20goods%2C%20Morgan%20Stanley's%20Zezas%20said.%20Service%20companies'%20business%20models%20can%20show%20resilience%20in%20the%20face%20of%20high%20tariffs.%20Services%20such%20as%20software%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20consulting%20don't%20rely%20on%20imported%20goods%20and%20don't%20face%20direct%20tariff%20repercussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDefensive%20stocks%20that%20provide%20essential%20goods%20and%20services%20will%20also%20outperform%2C%20as%20demand%20remains%20steady%20regardless%20of%20economic%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20doubt%20that%20the%20Trump%20agenda%20is%20an%20America%20First%20agenda%2C%26quot%3B%20Paul%20Stanley%2C%20the%20chief%20investment%20officer%20of%20Granite%20Bay%20Wealth%20Management%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20looking%20at%20more%20mid-cap%20stocks%2C%20which%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20domestic%20and%20industrial-focused.%20Industrials%2C%20financials%2C%20and%20healthcare%20tend%20to%20be%20very%20good%20US%20players%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Stanley%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20fixed-income%20side%2C%20Morgan%20Stanley%20identified%20US%20Treasurys%20as%20a%20solid%20bet%20in%20a%20high-tariff%20environment.%20In%20volatile%20times%2C%20investors%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-bond-market-trump-tariffs-economy-china-canada-mexico-yields-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflock%20to%20safe%20government-backed%20assets%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20as%20global%20trade%20tensions%20continue%20to%20rise%2C%20Zezas%20expects%20foreign%20investment%20to%20pour%20into%20US%20Treasurys%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Zezas%20is%20bullish%20on%20longer-duration%20fixed%20income.%20A%20more%20dovish%20rate%20policy%20could%20be%20in%20the%20cards%20as%20tariffs%20drag%20on%20growth.%20If%20interest%20rates%20come%20down%20in%20the%20future%2C%20then%20bond%20prices%20will%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBruce%20Kasman%2C%20JPMorgan's%20chief%20economist%20and%20global%20head%20of%20economic%20research%2C%20also%20sees%20room%20for%20rates%20to%20fall%20amid%20high%20tariffs%2C%20even%20in%20a%20hot%20inflation%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20the%20Fed%20will%20also%20display%20a%20heightened%20sensitivity%20to%20downside%20growth%20risks.%20While%20a%20faltering%20in%20labor%20demand%20is%20not%20in%20our%20forecast%2C%20the%20Fed%20will%20not%20hesitate%20to%20cut%20policy%20rates%20with%20elevated%20inflation%20if%20it%20sees%20a%20material%20threat%20to%20the%20expansion%2C%26quot%3B%20Kasman%20and%20his%20team%20wrote%20in%20a%20recent%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22493cff57-f9ec-4948-8570-9169072a605d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%A6and%20losers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELong-term%20tariffs%20will%20undeniably%20drag%20on%20economic%20growth.%20Morgan%20Stanley%20predicts%20that%20headl