%20had%20raised%20%243.5%20billion%20in%20fresh%20funding.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cmlee%40insider.com%20(Lee%20Chong%20Ming)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-deepseek-impact-ai-market-position-valuation-models-api-gtm-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20Is%20Elissa%20Slotkin%2C%20Former%20CIA%20Analyst%20Who%20Took%20On%20Trump%20In%20Congress%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESenator%20Elissa%20Slotkin%2C%20a%20first-term%20Democrat%20from%20Michigan%2C%20delivered%20a%20direct%20and%20measured%20response%20to%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20lengthy%20and%20combative%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Famerica-is-back-donald-trump-declares-in-explosive-speech-to-us-congress-7851654%5C%22%3Eaddress%20to%20Congress%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Speaking%20from%20Wyandotte%2C%20Michigan%2C%20she%20warned%20that%20Trump%20was%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20to%20make%20you%20pay%20in%20every%20part%20of%20your%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20arguing%20his%20policies%20would%20drive%20up%20healthcare%20costs%20and%20burden%20Americans%20financially.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Slotkin%2C%2048%2C%20who%20won%20a%20tough%20Senate%20race%20last%20year%2C%20took%20on%20the%20challenging%20task%20of%20countering%20a%20president%20she%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bcosying%20up%20to%20dictators%20like%20Vladimir%20Putin.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20is%20Elissa%20Slotkin%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EElissa%20Slotkin%20attended%20Cranbrook%20Kingswood%20School%20in%20Bloomfield%20Hills%20and%20later%20earned%20a%20Bachelor%20of%20Arts%20in%20Sociology%20from%20Cornell%20University%20in%201998.%20In%202003%2C%20she%20obtained%20a%20Master's%20in%20International%20Affairs%20from%20Columbia%20University's%20School%20of%20International%20and%20Public%20Affairs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFluent%20in%20Arabic%20and%20Swahili%2C%20she%20was%20recruited%20by%20the%20Central%20Intelligence%20Agency%20(CIA)%20after%20graduation.%20As%20a%20Middle%20East%20analyst%2C%20Ms%20Slotkin%20completed%20three%20tours%20in%20Iraq%20alongside%20the%20US%20military.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EShe%20went%20on%20to%20hold%20key%20national%20security%20roles%20in%20the%20White%20House%2C%20working%20on%20the%20Iraq%20portfolio%20under%20President%20George%20W%20Bush%20and%20later%20serving%20in%20the%20State%20Department%20and%20Department%20of%20Defence%20under%20President%20Barack%20Obama.%20She%20served%20as%20the%20Acting%20Assistant%20Secretary%20of%20Defence%20for%20International%20Security%20Affairs%20from%202015%20to%202017%2C%20handling%20critical%20matters%20like%20the%20fight%20against%20ISIS%20and%20US%20responses%20to%20Russian%20aggression.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMs%20Slotkin's%20decision%20to%20enter%20politics%20was%20influenced%20by%20her%20mother's%20condition%2C%20who%20had%20ovarian%20cancer%20and%20struggled%20with%20high%20healthcare%20costs%20due%20to%20pre-existing%20conditions.%20In%202018%2C%20she%20won%20a%20seat%20in%20the%20US%20House%20of%20Representatives%20as%20part%20of%20a%20wave%20of%20Democratic%20women%20with%20military%20or%20intelligence%20backgrounds.%20She%20flipped%20a%20Republican-held%20district%20in%20swing%20state%20Michigan.%20Throughout%20her%20congressional%20career%2C%20she%20opposed%20Donald%20Trump's%20policies.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%202024%2C%20Ms%20Slotkin%20ran%20for%20the%20US%20Senate%20and%20won%20in%20Michigan%20against%20former%20Congressman%20Mike%20Rogers.%20She%20became%20the%20youngest%20Democratic%20woman%20elected%20to%20the%20Senate%20at%2048.%20She%20is%20a%20member%20of%20key%20committees%2C%20including%20the%20Armed%20Forces%2C%20Homeland%20Security%2C%20Agriculture%2C%20and%20Veterans%20Affairs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Trump's%20Congressional%20speech%2C%20Ms%20Slotkin%20dismissed%20Trump's%20economic%20promises%2C%20pointing%20ou